ADD utopia.3151.a.desc:0 "The [fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural] are clearly dignitaries of some kind, discussing matters of state. Slowly, surely, the vision encroaches upon them while their alien speech is gradually transformed into words that have meaning to us."
CN2 utopia.3151.a.desc:0 " [fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 很明显是该种族中的高层人士，正在谈论着国家大事。我们的视野逐渐凝聚在这两人身上，他们所说的外星语言慢慢地被翻译成我们所明白的文字。"
ADD utopia.3151.b.desc:0 "The mind-glow of the two [fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural] is overwhelming. Like a blossoming flower, their minds open and are laid bare. It would be so easy to reach in."
CN2 utopia.3151.b.desc:0 "两位 [fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 的心灵光芒亮得差点闪瞎我们。他们的脑海犹如盛开的花朵，对我们彻底敞开。想要进入一探究竟简直是轻而易举。"
ADD utopia.3151.c.desc:0 "There. Technological secrets plucked from the recesses of their minds, as easy as one would copy a file from an unlocked computer. The [fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural] remain ignorant of the theft that has taken place within their very minds."
CN2 utopia.3151.c.desc:0 "他们脑海中储存的科技秘密被一个个取出，就像从电脑中复制文件一样简单。这些 [fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 依旧没有注意到自己脑海中的秘密正在被曝光。"
ADD utopia.3151.1.desc:0 "§H"...is mad. If she thinks that the people would be willing to accept even a momentary lapse in the living standards that they have grown accustomed to, there is..."§!"
CN2 utopia.3151.1.desc:0 "§H"……简直发神经。她要是以为人们会接受哪怕是一点点的生活质量降低，那她就实在是太拿……"§!"
ADD utopia.3151.2.desc:0 "§H"...is a disgrace. Imagine if the younger races were to even suspect that we no longer fully understand our own technology! We must..."§!"
CN2 utopia.3151.2.desc:0 "§H"……是耻辱啊。要是让附属种族们察觉到我们已经对自己的科技失去了理解，那种情况简直不敢想象！我们必须……"§!"
ADD utopia.3151.3.desc:0 "§H"...are growing more and more powerful. Elements of the Council are convinced that unless we take action..."§!"
CN2 utopia.3151.3.desc:0 "§H"……变得越来越强大了。议会认为我们再不采取行动的话……"§!"
ADD utopia.3151.4.desc:0 "§H"...don't care what the Council says. The upstarts are still millennia behind us, and their miserable fleets can no more threaten us than a Gazurian gnat could consume a Hilaxi fire lizard. There is no need for..."§!"
CN2 utopia.3151.4.desc:0 "§H"……不必在乎议会怎么说。那群人比起我们还差得远呢，他们那孱弱的舰队还不足以与我们抗衡。我们没必要去……"§!"
ADD utopia.3151.5.desc:0 "§H"...still think punitive actions are uncalled for. They are young and careless, but so were we once upon a time. There is still time for them to..."§!"
CN2 utopia.3151.5.desc:0 "§H"……觉得惩罚性措施是不必要的。他们还年少无知，我们以前不也是经历过同样的情况嘛。应该给他们机会去……"§!"
ADD utopia.3151.6.desc:0 "§H"...and that perhaps we should have taken steps to cull the younger races before they grew too powerful. I have to say that I agree with him, but the Council feels that it is too late now to..."§!"
CN2 utopia.3151.6.desc:0 "§H"……要我说就该趁附属种族变得太强大前先发制人。我很同意他的看法，但是议会认为现在已经太迟……"§!"
ADD utopia.3152.desc:0 "The [fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural] are clearly dignitaries of some kind, discussing matters of state. Slowly, surely, the vision encroaches upon them while their alien speech is gradually transformed into words that have meaning to us.\n\nSuddenly, the aliens go quiet and very still.\n\n§H"Can you feel it?"\n\n"Yes. Someone is watching."§!\n\nTheir eyes search the room until both of them are staring directly at us.\n\n§H"Remarkable. A psionic probe."§!\n\n§H"It appears [Root.GetSpeciesName] in origin. Quickly, activate the transplanar shield.§!"\n\nThe vision ends abruptly."
CN2 utopia.3152.desc:0 " [fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 很明显是该种族中的高层人士，正在谈论着国家大事。我们的视野逐渐凝聚在这两人身上，他们所说的外星语言慢慢地被翻译成我们所明白的文字。\n\n外星人们突然安静了下来。\n\n§H"你感觉到了么？\n\n"是的。有人在监视着我们。"§!他们四处张望，最后直溜溜地盯向我们的方向。\n\n§H"真是让人惊讶。竟然是个灵能探测器。"§!\n\n§H"看起来是属于 [Root.GetSpeciesName] 的。快，启动跨次元护盾。§!"\n\n画面就此中断。"
ADD utopia.3153.desc:0 "[Root.GetSpeciesNamePlural].\n\nDo not think that your loathsome attempt to invade the minds of our leaders has gone unnoticed.\n\nThere will be consequences."
CN2 utopia.3153.desc:0 " [Root.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 。\n\n别以为你们试图入侵我们领导人大脑的行为没有被察觉。 \n\n你们会有报应的，等着吧。"
ADD utopia.3053.a:0 "B-but... we can explain!"
CN2 utopia.3053.a:0 "不、不是那样子的……你听我们解释！"
ADD utopia.3160.desc:0 "A small, flickering star materializes inside the Shroud. It flies past at incredible speed, and for a second, it reveals itself as an alien ship of unknown configuration. Then it vanishes in a cloud of psionic energy as quickly as it appeared.\n\nCan it be? Is it possible to physically enter the Shroud and then emerge somewhere else entirely in normal space?"
CN2 utopia.3160.desc:0 "一个闪亮的小星星突然出现在灵能界。它以飞快的速度瞬间飞过，在那么一刹那间，我们看见了它的实际形态——原来那是一艘未知外星种族的舰船。它随后瞬间消失在灵能云团之中。这真的可能吗？难道真的有办法以实体进入灵能界，然后重新出现在正常空间的其他地方？"
ADD utopia.3160.a:0 "§YLinger for a while.§!"
CN2 utopia.3160.a:0 "§Y多呆一会儿。§!"
ADD utopia.3161.desc:0 "Yet another flickering star suddenly appears, but this time we are ready. It is indeed an alien ship, unlike any that has ever been seen in our galaxy. As it flies past us, we feel the mind-glow of its crew, and their secrets are ours.\n\nA Psionic Jump Drive. How ingenious."
CN2 utopia.3161.desc:0 "又是一个闪亮的小星星突然出现，然而这一次我们已经准备妥当。看见了！的确是一艘外星人舰船，其外形闻所未闻。它飞过我们身边时，我们清晰地感觉到对方船员的心灵光芒，他们的秘密全数落入了我们脑海中。\n\n竟然是灵能跃迁引擎。太机智了。"
ADD utopia.3161.name:0 "§GPsionic Jump Drives§!"
CN2 utopia.3161.name:0 "§G灵能跃迁引擎§!"
ADD utopia.3162.desc:0 "Yet another flickering star suddenly appears, but this time we are ready. It is indeed an alien ship, unlike any that has ever been seen in our galaxy. As it flies past us, we attempt to merge with the mind-glow of its crew, but their intellects are darker and more alien than any we have yet encountered.\n\nNot only are we repelled from their vessel, but the psionic feedback from their violent rejection has followed us out of the Shroud! The sub-light travel speed of our starships has been momentarily reduced."
CN2 utopia.3162.desc:0 "又是一个闪亮的小星星突然出现，然而这一次我们已经准备妥当。看见了！的确是一艘外星人舰船，其外形闻所未闻。它飞过我们身边时，我们试图跟对方船员的心灵光芒合并，但是对方的智慧比我们所见过的更加黑暗和陌生。\n\n他们不仅把我们驱逐出了舰船，对方的灵能反噬甚至一路跟踪着我们退出灵能界！我们飞船的亚光速航行速度也因此暂时性被降低了。"
ADD utopia.3170.desc:0 "In one of the lower planes of the Shroud, we encounter a spirit that has ensconced itself behind some kind of powerful psionic shield.\n\n§P"LEAVE."§!"
CN2 utopia.3170.desc:0 "我们在灵能界的某个较低次元遇到了一个被强大的灵能护盾所包围着的生命。\n\n§P"离开这里。"\n§!"
ADD utopia.3170.a:0 "§YAttempt to penetrate the shield.§!"
CN2 utopia.3170.a:0 "§Y尝试击穿对方的护盾。§!"
ADD utopia.3171.name:0 "§GPsionic Shields§!"
CN2 utopia.3171.name:0 "§G灵能护盾§!"
ADD utopia.3171.desc:0 "We did not venture this deep into the Shroud only to be turned back now. After channeling all of their psionic might, our telepaths were able to form a breach in the shield large enough for some of them to peer through.\n\nWe do not know what those telepaths saw on the other side of the shield, but it was enough to permanently unhinge their minds. Their sacrifice was not in vain, however, as the act of breaching the shield taught us how to generate a similar force field. If the technique can be refined, we may be able to form psionic shields large enough to encompass entire starships..."
CN2 utopia.3171.desc:0 "我们冒了天大的险进入灵能界不是为了此刻打退堂鼓的。我们的通灵者在凝聚了所有的灵能后，终于成功在护盾上打开了一个小小的缺口，可以让部分通灵者窥视里面的光景。\n\n我们不知道这些通灵者到底看见了什么，但是他们最后都精神失常了。不过他们的牺牲不是白费的，因为击穿这个护盾的过程让我们学习到了如何生成一个类似的力场护盾。只要优化一下这个技术，我们应该就可以生成出一个巨大到可以覆盖整艘战舰的灵能护盾……"
ADD utopia.3172.desc:0 "Our telepaths, already exhausted from having ventured this deeply into the Shroud, failed to channel enough psionic strength to breach the shield. The failed attempt seems to have provoked the spirit!\n\n§P"YOU WERE AMPLY WARNED, MAGGOTS. AS YOU TRIED TO INVADE MY WORLD, I SHALL NOW BRING RUIN TO YOURS."§!"
CN2 utopia.3172.desc:0 "我们的通灵者在灵能界奔波劳顿后已经筋疲力尽，无法引导足够的灵能力量去击穿对方的装甲。但我们的举动彻底激怒了该灵魂生命！ \n\n§P"蝼蚁们，我警告过你们的。既然你们试图入侵我的世界，那我就以牙还牙毁灭掉你们的世界吧。"\n§!"
ADD utopia.3180.desc:0 "The concept of time, as we know it, is alien to this part of the Shroud. What can seem like centuries here may equal mere hours or even minutes in the real world. If one knows where to look, it is even possible to glimpse into the future...\n\nPrecognition is one of the surest paths to madness for a telepath, so we must use caution."
CN2 utopia.3180.desc:0 "这一部分灵能界的时间概念绝对跟我们世界的不同。这里所经历的一整个世纪，对于现实世界来说仅仅是数个小时甚至数分钟。也许只要找到适当的方式，我们可以窥视到未来的世界……\n\n对于通灵者来说，探究预知能力几乎必定会招致精神失常。所以我们必须谨慎行事。"
ADD utopia.3180.a:0 "§YMeditate here for a moment.§!"
CN2 utopia.3180.a:0 "§Y在这里冥想一阵子。§!"
ADD utopia.3181.desc:0 "A limited precognitive connection to the Shroud can be maintained without risking insanity, but the massive influx of probability data is too overwhelming to be of much practical use.\n\nStill, if a digital interface could be devised to interpret this data, it could potentially be applied to improve the performance of our starships' combat computers..."
CN2 utopia.3181.desc:0 "跟灵能界的预知能力建立有限的联系的确可以避免通灵者精神失常，但是庞大数量的概率数据却无法被有效地利用起来。\n\n不过要是可以开发出一个电子接口来分析这些数据，那我们舰船的作战计算机也许就可以获得质的提升……"
ADD utopia.3181.name:0 "§GPrecognition Interface§!"
CN2 utopia.3181.name:0 "§G预知接口§!"
ADD utopia.3182.desc:0 "As we feared, madness has overtaken our telepaths. All at once, their minds have been opened to the inconceivable multitude of options and probabilities that exist both in the past and the future.\n\nEvery single variation and scenario, no matter how colossal or miniscule the difference between them, is being endlessly repeated inside their brains. They have been reduced to a state of permanent catatonia.\n\nIt will be some time before the Conclave of Telepaths can muster the psionic strength needed to reach into the Shroud again."
CN2 utopia.3182.desc:0 "果然，我们的通灵者全都精神失常了。他们的脑海在一瞬间被无数种对过去和未来的选项和可能性狂轰滥炸。\n\n每一种不同的选项和场景，无论差别有多巨大或微小，都不断地在他们的脑海中反复运算。他们彻底进入永久性紧张症状态中。通灵会怕是很长一段时间都无法恢复足够的实力去再次踏足灵能界了。"
ADD utopia.3190.desc:0 "We have found a tiny space within the Shroud that has a concentration of psionic energy that is of a magnitude we have never before seen. Any psychic that managed to successfully tap into this pocket of raw energy would become immensely powerful... but there is only enough for a single individual, and there are risks involved.\n\nThere are only three individuals in the entire [Root.GetName] that possess the psionic strength needed to tap into this energy pocket with any hope of survival. Who should it be?"
CN2 utopia.3190.desc:0 "我们在灵能界中找到了一处小型空间，里面充斥着一种浓郁到闻所未闻的灵能源。任何成功吸收这团原始能源的灵能者都会变得异常强大……问题是这团能源只足够强化一个人，而且还有风险性。\n\n放眼整个 [Root.GetName] ，只有三个人拥有足够的灵能能力去试图吸收这团能源。那到底该派谁上阵呢？"
ADD utopia.3190.1.a:0 "§GGo with [leader_1.GetName]§!"
CN2 utopia.3190.1.a:0 "§G派出 [leader_1.GetName] §!"
