CN2 utopia.3190.3.c:0 "§R派出 [leader_3.GetName] §!"
ADD utopia.3191.desc:0 "It... it is done. The entire Shroud seems to shudder as the psionic energy pocket is drained, and its power transferred to [chosen_leader.GetName].\n\nOnly a handful of individuals in the history of the entire galaxy has been gifted with psionic strength of this magnitude. May the Spirits have mercy on our souls."
CN2 utopia.3191.desc:0 "竟……竟然成功了。整个灵能界在这股灵能被汲取的一瞬间颤动了起来，灵能源成功转移到 [chosen_leader.GetName] 身上了。\n\n整个宇宙有史以来拥有如此庞大灵能力量的人物屈指可数。愿灵魂庇佑我们的心灵。"
ADD utopia.3192.desc:0 "The entire Shroud seems to shudder as the immense psionic energies contained within the pocket are transferred to [chosen_leader.GetName].\n\nUnfortunately, [chosen_leader.GetHerHis] mind was unable to cope with the stress. Perhaps no living thing was meant to be in possession of such power. [chosen_leader.GetName] passed away in a large explosion of psionic energy that killed all who were nearby."
CN2 utopia.3192.desc:0 "随着能源团里的灵能被转移到 [chosen_leader.GetName] 身上，整个灵能界都颤动了起来。\n\n然而非常不幸， [chosen_leader.GetHerHis] 的精神无法应付这份压迫感。也许如此的力量本来就不是任何生物可以掌握的。 [chosen_leader.GetName] 在一场庞大的灵能爆炸中陨落，甚至一并带走了周围的所有人。"
ADD utopia.3193.desc:0 "The entire Shroud seems to shudder as the immense psionic energies contained within the pocket are transferred to [chosen_leader.GetName].\n\nAlthough the transfer was successful, [chosen_leader.GetName] has been... transformed... into some kind of being of pure energy.\n\n§P"...WHAT... WHAT HAVE YOU... DONE... TO ME..."§!\n\n§P"YOU... WILL... ALL... PAY..."§!"
CN2 utopia.3193.desc:0 "随着能源团里的灵能被转移到 [chosen_leader.GetName] 身上，整个灵能界都颤动了起来。\n\n虽然能源转移很成功，但是 [chosen_leader.GetName] 似乎……似乎被转化成了……一种原始能源体。\n\n§P"……你……你们对我……做……了什么……"§!§P"我……我要……你们……付出代价……\n§!"
ADD utopia.3200.1.desc:0 "The void here shimmers with power. Let us rest a while."
CN2 utopia.3200.1.desc:0 "此处的虚空充斥着能源。我们在此稍事休息一下吧。"
ADD utopia.3200.2.desc:0 "The path we followed has come to an abrupt end. We can go no farther."
CN2 utopia.3200.2.desc:0 "我们所取的航道突然戛然而止。无法继续前进了。"
ADD utopia.3200.3.desc:0 "Something speaks to us here. Something wonderful."
CN2 utopia.3200.3.desc:0 "这里有东西试图跟我们交流。某种很神奇的存在。"
ADD utopia.3200.4.desc:0 "For reasons we cannot fathom, we have been drawn to this corner of the Shroud. Why?"
CN2 utopia.3200.4.desc:0 "不知为何，我们被吸引到灵能界的这个角落来。这究竟是什么原因呢？"
ADD utopia.3200.5.desc:0 "For a fleeting moment, we are lost and a sense of utter panic washes over us as we contemplate an eternity spent within the Shroud. Then we regain our footing, and the terror recedes."
CN2 utopia.3200.5.desc:0 "在那一瞬间，我们迷失了，一种彻底的恐慌感涌进了我们全身，感觉自己像在灵能界中度过了一辈子那么漫长的时间。等我们清醒过来时，恐慌感才逐渐退散。"
ADD utopia.3200.6.desc:0 "A flock of spirits glowing with dazzling colors that do not exist in normal space dance around us for several hours as we venture deeper into the Shroud. The spectacle is enjoyable, until the realization hits us - we are being herded."
CN2 utopia.3200.6.desc:0 "在我们深入灵能界的途中，一群只存在于灵能界的散发着七彩光芒的灵魂体围绕着我们舞蹈了好几个小时。它们看起来是那么的赏心悦目，直到我们突然醒悟——我们一路是被它们驱赶着到这里来的。"
ADD utopia.3200.7.desc:0 "A shard of perfect crystal floats here, rotating slowly around its own axis. As we approach, it shatters into a thousand pieces."
CN2 utopia.3200.7.desc:0 "一片完美的宝石碎片漂浮在此处，绕着自己的轴线缓慢旋转着。在我们接近它时，它突然碎裂成了千万个碎片。"
ADD utopia.3200.8.desc:0 "The corpse of a dead [Root.GetSpeciesName] tumbles through the void ahead. The putrid carcass emits a shrill screech before it vanishes out of sight."
CN2 utopia.3200.8.desc:0 "一具 [Root.GetSpeciesName] 的尸体在前方的虚空中飘过。这具腐烂的尸体发出了一道刺耳的尖叫声，随后消失无踪。"
ADD utopia.3200.9.desc:0 "We cannot be certain this is really happening. Are we truly in the Shroud, or is one of us experiencing an acute psychotic breakdown?"
CN2 utopia.3200.9.desc:0 "我们不确定这是不是真的。我们真的是身处灵能界中吗？还是说是我们其中一人经历了严重的精神崩溃。"
ADD terraforming_candidate_category:0 "Ancient Signs of Life"
CN2 terraforming_candidate_category:0 "古老的生命迹象"
ADD terraforming_candidate_category_desc:0 "This barren and lifeless world is showing signs of once having supported a biosphere."
CN2 terraforming_candidate_category_desc:0 "这个贫瘠而又无生命的星球上的种种痕迹显示它曾经是一个生机蓬勃的世界。"
ADD anomaly.2575.name:0 "Terraforming Candidate Discovered"
CN2 anomaly.2575.name:0 "发现适合环境改造的星球"
ADD anomaly.2575.desc.intro:0 "Our detailed survey of [From.GetName] has revealed that it may once have supported life in the distant past. There are significant deposits of frozen water at the polar ice caps and beneath the [From.GetPlanetMoon]'s surface. The existence of valley networks suggest that the water may once have flowed freely."
CN2 anomaly.2575.desc.intro:0 "我们对 [From.GetName] 仔细考察后发现，这里曾经有过生命的迹象。 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 的极地和地表下都拥有着相当庞大的冰水储量。而且这里的山谷痕迹都显示着曾经有河流流过的迹象。"
ADD anomaly.2575.desc.1:0 "$anomaly.2575.desc.intro$\n\nTerraforming this [From.GetPlanetMoon] would theoretically be possible, but we do not yet possess the technology to accomplish this monumental task within a realistic timeframe."
CN2 anomaly.2575.desc.1:0 "$anomaly.2575.desc.intro$环境改造 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 星球在理论上是可行的，但是我们尚未掌握在短期内完成这个庞大项目的技术。"
ADD anomaly.2575.desc.2:0 "$anomaly.2575.desc.intro$\n\nThe energy costs would be daunting, but we do have the technology to gradually terraform this [From.GetPlanetMoon] into something that would support life once again."
CN2 anomaly.2575.desc.2:0 "$anomaly.2575.desc.intro$虽然能源消耗会很恐怖，但是我们的确可以将 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 环境改造为可居住的星球。"
ADD anomaly.2575.desc.3:0 "$anomaly.2575.desc.intro$\n\nUnfortunately the §YDyson Sphere§! in this system has removed any possibility of restoring the planet."
ADD utopia.3300.desc:0 "There is a presence here, occupying this entire part of the Shroud. We have met spirits before, but this is something else, something vastly more powerful... something far more ancient.\n\nIt seems unaware of us as of yet. Perhaps it is sleeping. Perhaps we are simply beneath its notice.\n\nPerhaps we should leave."
CN2 utopia.3300.desc:0 "这一部分的灵能界是由某个个体所掌控。我们见过的灵魂多去了，但这个却很不同。这个实在强大得多，而且……非常古老。\n\n它似乎还没有注意到我们的到来。也许它是在沉睡状态中。也许我们根本不足以让它在意。我们也许应该离开这里。"
ADD utopia.3300.1.a:0 "§GAttempt to communicate with the presence§!"
CN2 utopia.3300.1.a:0 "§G尝试与该个体交流§!"
ADD utopia.3300.1.b:0 "§YAttempt to communicate with the presence§!"
CN2 utopia.3300.1.b:0 "§Y尝试与该个体交流§!"
ADD utopia.3300.1.c:0 "§RAttempt to communicate with the presence§!"
CN2 utopia.3300.1.c:0 "§R尝试与该个体交流§!"
ADD utopia.3300.1.d:0 "§G[chosen_one.GetName] will speak to the presence§!"
CN2 utopia.3300.1.d:0 "§G派 [chosen_one.GetName] 去跟该个体交流§!"
ADD utopia.3301.desc:0 "As we reach out for the presence, we can feel it stirring, its attention now fully on us. It does not seem to appreciate being disturbed.\n\nA wave of energy lashes at our telepaths, causing great agony to some and knocking others unconscious. We have no choice but to withdraw from the Shroud for the time being."
CN2 utopia.3301.desc:0 "在我们试图接近该个体时，我们感觉到了它的波动。对方终于注意到我们了，但是它似乎很不开心被打搅。一股能源冲击向我们的通灵者，把他们一部分人彻底击晕，而其余人则痛苦呻吟。我们别无他法只能暂时退出灵能界。"
ADD utopia.3302.desc:0 "As we reach out for the presence, we can feel it stirring, its attention now fully on us. It does not seem to appreciate being disturbed.\n\nAn enormous wave of psionic energy crashes against us, blacking out the senses of our telepaths. When they come to, they notice one of their number is missing. §Y[leader_to_kill.GetName]§! is nowhere to be found, and where [leader_to_kill.GetSheHe] was standing there is now only the psionic trace of a small rift, as though the entity reached out into our world and dragged [leader_to_kill.GetHerHim] into the Shroud for... well, who knows what reason or purpose, really.\n\nNo matter its reasons for taking [leader_to_kill.GetHerHim], it seems doubtful that we will ever see [leader_to_kill.GetName] again."
CN2 utopia.3302.desc:0 "在我们试图接近该个体时，我们感觉到了它的波动。对方终于注意到我们了，但是它似乎很不开心被打搅。 \n\n一股庞大的灵能向我们猛烈压制而来，导致我们的通灵者彻底昏迷。当他们终于恢复意识时，才发现其中一位同伴失踪了。§Y [leader_to_kill.GetName] §!不见了，其之前所站立的地方只剩下一个小型裂缝所残留下的灵能。感觉就像该存在进入了我们的世界将 [leader_to_kill.GetName] 拽进了灵能界……它为什么这么做那就不得而知了。\n\n不管对方是出于什么原因掳走了 [leader_to_kill.GetName] ，我们很可能再也见不到 [leader_to_kill.GetName] 了。"
ADD utopia.3304.desc:0 "As we reach out for the presence, the minds of our telepaths are filled with a chorus of voices. No more than soft whispers at first, the cacophony grows in intensity, a thousand voices speaking in unison. \n\nThe voices introduce themselves as the §YWhisperers in the Void§!. It - they - claim to be privy to all knowledge whispered in secrecy from one mortal to another, and offer to share of these secrets with us...\n\n§YIf we will only allow them into our consciousness.§!\n\nA trifling price, they assure us. We will barely even notice their presence.\n\nThere is an urgency to their tone."
CN2 utopia.3304.desc:0 "在我们试图接近该个体时，我们的通灵者的脑海中响起了一道道整齐的声音。一开始是柔和的细语声，接着就越来越响亮，直到变成成千上万道声音同时响起一般。\n\n这个声音自称为§Y虚空低语者§!。它——或者它们——自称听得见凡人们之间互相细语的秘密，并愿意把这些秘密拿出来跟我们分享。§Y前提是我们愿意将其纳入我们的意识中。§!他们向我们担保，这个代价是微不足道的。我们几乎不会察觉到他们的存在。他们的语气似乎有点急迫。"
ADD utopia.3304.a:0 "§YForm a Covenant with the Whisperers in the Void§!"
CN2 utopia.3304.a:0 "§Y与虚空低语者签订契约§!"
ADD utopia.3305.desc:0 "The presence welcomes us with genial familiarity. It speaks not so much in words but in visions, concepts, ideas. It seeps into the minds of our telepaths, so gently and smoothly that one might think it had always been there. A flurry of images flash before their eyes.\n\nThe presence is known as the §YComposer of Strands§!, and it regards our biological forms with curious interest. It shows us a variety of ways in which they can be grown, changed. Improved. Evolved.\n\n§YIf we will only take it into our flesh.§!\n\nIt waits for our answer patiently, affectionately. Like a doting father waiting on his favorite child."
CN2 utopia.3305.desc:0 "该个体以亲切友好的姿态欢迎我们。它并不多言，而是以幻视、观点、概念进行着交流。它渗透入我们的精神，感应我们的心灵，轻柔无痕宛如从一开始就存在于那里。而他们的眼前闪掠过一系列图像。这种个体被称为§Y丝状体编织者§!，它们对我们的生物形态充满好奇，并向我们展示了其生长、转化、发展、进化的多种方式。§Y前提是我们愿意将其纳入我们的身体里。§!它充满慈爱地耐心等待着我们的回应，宛如一位宽和的父亲等待自己最宠溺的孩子。"
ADD utopia.3305.a:0 "§YForm a Covenant with the Composer of Strands§!"
CN2 utopia.3305.a:0 "§Y与丝状体编织者签订契约§!"
ADD utopia.3306.desc:0 "As we reach out for the presence, we sense a great hunger. The presence wastes no time, not words. It is the §YEater of Worlds§! and it wishes to devour us.\n\nOnly some of us, though. No more than we can spare. In exchange, it will grant us great powers. It will teach us its hunger, its rage. It will shape them into psionic weapons that can overcome any foe.\n\n§YIf we will only let it feed on us.§!\n\nIt sounds impatient to begin."
CN2 utopia.3306.desc:0 "在接近该个体时，我们感受到了一种强烈的饥渴。它没有在言语上浪费时间。这是§Y世界吞噬者§!，它想要吞噬我们。不过只是吞噬我们的一部分，不会超出我们无法承受的范围。作为交换，它将赐予我们强大的力量。它会教导我们它的饥渴、它的愤怒。这种知识可以其转化为能够击败一切敌人的灵能武器。§Y前提是我们需要允许它以我们为食。§!它开始迫不及待了。"
ADD utopia.3306.a:0 "§YForm a Covenant with the Eater of Worlds§!"
CN2 utopia.3306.a:0 "§Y与世界吞噬者签订契约§!"
ADD utopia.3307.desc:0 "Before we can reach out for the presence, it reaches out for us. Its thoughts coil and twist themselves around the minds of our telepaths, bargaining, cajoling. It is the §YInstrument of Desire§! and it will grant us wealth, power, prestige... all that we have ever desired. All that we will ever desire.\n\nThe cost? A small matter, little more than a cover fee. It only wants what's best for us. It will help us, guide us, direct our ambitions and dreams.\n\n§YIf we will only accept it into our hearts.§!\n\nIt is confident that we will say yes. How could we possibly not say yes?"
CN2 utopia.3307.desc:0 "在我们向该个体靠近之前它便率先接近了我们。它的思想在我们的意识周围缠绕蜷曲，花言巧语，循循善诱。它名为§Y欲望操纵者§!，它能够赐予我们财富、权力、威望……我们曾渴望并所能渴望的一切。代价？简直不值一提，不过是些许的意思费。它只希望我们一切都好。它会帮助我们，引导我们，指引我们的愿景与梦想。§Y前提是我们需要接纳它进入我们的内心。§!它对于我们的答案胸有成竹。我们怎么能说不呢？"
ADD utopia.3307.a:0 "§YForm a Covenant with the Instrument of Desire§!"
CN2 utopia.3307.a:0 "§Y与欲望操纵者签订契约§!"
ADD utopia.3308.desc:0 "The presence was waiting for us. It is §RThe End of the Cycle§! and it has always been waiting for us. Our telepaths suddenly speak in unison, a dozen voices in a perfect chorus: §R"IT IS NOT YET YOUR TIME."§! A pause. §R"BUT IT COULD BE."§!\n\nNothing more is said, but a bargain has been offered - we know that much. Power, knowledge and wealth beyond measure are ours for the taking.\n\n§RIf we will only bring forth the End.§!"
CN2 utopia.3308.desc:0 "它在等待我们。这个名为§R循环之终§!的存在一直都在等候我们。在我们的心中突然同时响起一个声音，一个由无数道声音所组成的完美和声：§R"汝等之日尚未至。"§!接着停顿片刻。§R\n"或是此刻未可知。"\n§!\n\n寥寥数语，但我们很清楚对方已经抛出了交易的橄榄枝。超乎想象的力量、知识以及财富已经唾手可得。§R前提是我们需要迎接终结。§!"
ADD utopia.3308.a:0 "§RForm a Covenant with the End of the Cycle§!"
CN2 utopia.3308.a:0 "§R与循环之终签订契约§!"
ADD utopia.3310.name:0 "Covenant Formed"
CN2 utopia.3310.name:0 "契约已签订"
ADD utopia.3320.name:0 "The End of the Cycle: §RReckoning§!"
CN2 utopia.3320.name:0 "循环之终：§R审判日§!"
ADD utopia.3320.desc.a:0 "Our time is up. For fifty years, we have benefitted from the immense power given to us by the §REnd of the Cycle§!. We knew there would be a price to pay, but we thought it might be one we could bear, or that we could find some way to avoid paying it.\n\nIt was not, and we could not.\n\nThe price we have paid is everything. In an instant, so fast there is no time to react, let alone respond, the [Root.GetName] is... gone. Where once there was thriving colonies, there is now only death. Where once mighty fleets crossed the void, there is only ghosts and debris. All devoured by the End. All taken by the Shroud.\n\nAll that remains of our empire is a group of exiles led by §Y[Root.GetRulerName]§!, a powerful psionic who saw the end coming and led a small part of our population into hiding on a world not marked by the End.\n\nAs if having our empire destroyed overnight wasn't bad enough, a massive Shroud entity has manifested itself in space above [former_capital.GetName]. Made immensely powerful by the devoured consciousnesses of our psionics, it now roams the galaxy seeking further prey."
CN2 utopia.3320.desc.a:0 "我们的日子到头了。五十年来，我们从§R循环之终§!赐予的无尽知识中获益匪浅。我们深知这一切终须付出代价，本来心存侥幸认为我们付得起，或能想方设法逃避。然而代价太大，我们亦无法逃避。我们需要付出的是我们的全部。转瞬之间，我们甚至都还没来得及反应，遑论进行应对，整个 [Root.GetName] 就……荡然无存了。曾经欣欣向荣的殖民地如今只有死亡留存，原本叱咤虚空的强大舰队现在也只剩下幽灵与残骸。一切都被终结，一切都被灵能界粉碎。帝国仅存的只有一组由§Y [Root.GetRulerName] §!所率领的难民。这位强大的灵能者预见了这一日的到来，带领着我们的一小部分人口来到了一个没有被终结标记的世界。然而让我们的帝国一夕之间不复存在似乎还不够糟，在 [former_capital.GetName] 上空出现了一个巨大的灵能体。它因吞噬了我们的灵能意识而变得威力无穷，如今正在星河间游荡，搜寻着下一个猎物。"
ADD utopia.3320.desc.b:0 "Our time is up.\n\nFor fifty years, we have benefitted from the immense power given to us by the §REnd of the Cycle§!. We knew there would be a price to pay, but we thought it might be one we could bear, or that we could find some way to avoid paying it.\n\nIt was not, and we could not.\n\nThe price we have paid is everything. In an instant, so fast there is no time to react, let alone respond, the [Root.GetName] is... gone. Where once there was thriving colonies, there is now only death. Where once mighty fleets crossed the void, there is only ghosts and debris. All devoured by the End. All taken by the Shroud.\n\nNot only have we been utterly destroyed, a massive Shroud entity has also manifested itself in space above [former_capital.GetName]. Made immensely powerful by the devoured consciousnesses of our psionics, it now roams the galaxy seeking further prey. At least we will not be there to see it finish what we started."
CN2 utopia.3320.desc.b:0 "我们的日子到头了。五十年来，我们从§R循环之终§!赐予的无尽知识中获益匪浅。我们深知这一切终须付出代价，本来心存侥幸认为我们付得起，或能想方设法逃避。然而代价太大，我们亦无法逃避。我们需要付出的是我们的全部。转瞬之间，我们甚至都还没来得及反应，遑论进行应对，整个 [Root.GetName] 就……荡然无存了。曾经欣欣向荣的殖民地如今只有死亡留存，原本叱咤虚空的强大舰队现在也只剩下幽灵与残骸。一切都被终结，一切都被灵能界粉碎。不仅我们被彻底毁灭，在 [former_capital.GetName] 之上还诞生了一个巨大的灵能体。它因吞噬了我们的灵能意识而变得威力无穷，如今正在星河间游荡，搜寻着下一个猎物。至少我们不会在场亲眼目睹它是如何结束我们当初所开始的一切。"
ADD utopia.3320.opt.a:0 "What have we done...?"
CN2 utopia.3320.opt.a:0 "我们都闯了什么弥天大祸啊……？"
ADD utopia.3321.desc.a:0 "For fifty years we have known that something was wrong about the §Y[From.GetName]§!. Fifty years ago, their industrial output, the effectiveness of their science... everything about their empire suddenly and inexplicably experienced a massive increase in productivity and effectiveness, as if they were blessed by some unseen power.\n\nAs it turns out, it was not so much a blessing but a curse. Fifty years ago, the §Y[From.GetName]§! signed away their future and now the debt has come due.\n\nIn an instant, so fast there is no time to react, let alone respond, the [From.GetName] is... gone. Where once there was thriving colonies, there is now only death. Where once mighty fleets crossed the void, there is only ghosts and debris. Even our empire wasn't untouched in the disaster, with some of our own worlds that were previously under [From.GetAdj] rule destroyed along with the rest.\n\nWhat's worse, the death of the [From.GetName] seems to have birthed some sort of immensely powerful energy being in the space above their former capital.\n\nIt appears to be hungry."
CN2 utopia.3321.desc.a:0 "这五十年来，我们一直都怀疑§Y [From.GetName] §!非常不对劲。在五十年前他们的工业产值、科研效率……所有的方方面面都在一夜之间产生了巨大的飞跃，仿佛被某种不可见的力量加持了一般。从结果看来，这可不是什么庇佑，而是一个诅咒。五十年前，§Y [From.GetName] §!抵押了他们的未来，而如今他们需要偿还债务了。转瞬之间，都来不及反应，更别说做出回应， [Root.GetName] 就这么……荡然无存了。曾经欣欣向荣的殖民地如今只有死亡留存，原本叱咤虚空的强大舰队现在也只剩下幽灵与残骸。即便是我们帝国被这个灾难殃及，原先处于 [From.GetAdj] 统治下的几个当前属于我们的星球也随他们灰飞烟灭了。这还不算最糟的， [From.GetName] 上的死亡似乎导致其原本的首都上空诞生出了某种极为强大的能源存在。它已经开始蠢蠢欲动。"
ADD utopia.3321.desc.b:0 "For fifty years we have known that something was wrong about the §Y[From.GetName]§!. Fifty years ago, their industrial output, the effectiveness of their science... everything about their empire suddenly and inexplicably experienced a massive increase in productivity and effectiveness, as if they were blessed by some unseen power.\n\nAs it turns out, it was not so much a blessing but a curse. Fifty years ago, the §Y[From.GetName]§! signed away their future and now the debt has come due.\n\nIn an instant, so fast there is no time to react, let alone respond, the [From.GetName] is... gone. Where once there was thriving colonies, there is now only death. Where once mighty fleets crossed the void, there is only ghosts and debris.\n\nWhat's worse, the death of the [From.GetName] seems to have birthed some sort of immensely powerful energy being in the space above their former capital.\n\nNot satisfied with ending the [From.GetAdj] civilization, it now wanders from world to world, destroying all in its path."
CN2 utopia.3321.desc.b:0 "这五十年来，我们一直都怀疑§Y [From.GetName] §!非常不对劲。在五十年前他们的工业产值、科研效率……所有的方方面面都在一夜之间产生了巨大的飞跃，仿佛被某种不可见的力量加持了一般。 \n\n从结果看来，这可不是什么庇佑，而是一个诅咒。五十年前，§Y [From.GetName] §!抵押了他们的未来，如今要偿清债务了。转瞬之间，都来不及反应，更别说做出回应， [Root.GetName] 就这么……荡然无存了。曾经欣欣向荣的殖民地如今只有死亡留存，原本叱咤虚空的强大舰队现在也只剩下幽灵与残骸。这还不算最糟的， [From.GetName] 上的死亡似乎导致其原本的首都上空诞生出了某种极为强大的能源存在。它并不满足于仅仅终结 [From.GetAdj] 的文明，如今已经开始在星球间游荡，所到之处皆是末日。"
ADD utopia.3321.opt.a:0 "What have they done!?"
CN2 utopia.3321.opt.a:0 "他们都闯了什么弥天大祸？！"
ADD utopia.3324.name:0 "The End of the Cycle: §RShrouded§!"
CN2 utopia.3324.name:0 "循环之终：§R化为灵能§!"
ADD utopia.3324.desc:0 "We have been unable to stop the monstrous energy being from enveloping §Y[Root.GetName]§!. The planet and everyone living on it has been fully overtaken by The Shroud."
CN2 utopia.3324.desc:0 "我们无法阻止这般强大的能源体笼罩§Y [Root.GetName] §!。整个星球和星球上的生命都全部被灵能界统领了。"
ADD utopia.3324.opt.a:0 "Horrible!"
CN2 utopia.3324.opt.a:0 "太可怕了！"
ADD utopia.3331.name:0 "Whisperers in the Void: §RCoping§!"
CN2 utopia.3331.name:0 "虚空低语者：§R应对§!"
ADD utopia.3331.desc:0 "Though the secrets imparted to our people by the Whisperers are great use, some of them are also quite disturbing. Dealing with the stress of knowing too much can be difficult and have caused an increasing number among our population, including §Y[leader_target.GetTitle] [leader_target.GetName]§! to turn to substance abuse as a means to cope."
CN2 utopia.3331.desc:0 "尽管低语者传授给我们人民的秘密作用重大，但同时也十分令人不安。所知太多而造成的压力很难消减，这导致有人开始滥用药物来应对此问题，连§Y [leader_target.GetTitle]  [leader_target.GetName] §!也不例外。"
ADD utopia.3331.opt.a:0 "That is unfortunate."
CN2 utopia.3331.opt.a:0 "这太不幸了。"
ADD utopia.3332.name:0 "Whisperers in the Void: §RSuicide§!"
CN2 utopia.3332.name:0 "虚空低语者：§R自杀§!"
ADD utopia.3332.desc:0 "Though the secrets imparted to our people by the Whisperers are great use, some of them are also quite disturbing, particularly those shared with individuals of importance. §Y[leader_target.GetTitle] [leader_target.GetName]§!, unable to cope with the stress any longer, has taken [leader_target.GetHerHim] own life."
CN2 utopia.3332.desc:0 "尽管低语者传授给我们人民的秘密作用重大，但同时也十分令人不安，尤其是那些只分享给重要人士的知识。§Y [leader_target.GetTitle]  [leader_target.GetName] §!无法再承受这种压力，了结了 [leader_target.GetHerHim] 自己的性命。"
ADD utopia.3332.opt.a:0 "A tragedy."
CN2 utopia.3332.opt.a:0 "真是一场悲剧。"
ADD utopia.3333.name:0 "Whisperers in the Void: §RMadness§!"
CN2 utopia.3333.name:0 "虚空低语者：§R疯狂§!"
ADD utopia.3333.desc:0 "Ever since we invited the Whisperers into our minds, mental illness and unexplainable acts of violence have been on the rise among our psionic population. For the most part, it has been controllable, but recently things have gotten out of hand. A minor violent incident on §Y[planet_target.GetName]§! turned into a riot, and now the unrest and violence is spreading all across the planet, causing a great deal of death and destruction."
CN2 utopia.3333.desc:0 "自从我们邀请低语者进入我们的意识以来，精神疾病以及无法解释的暴力行为在我们的灵能人口中不断发生。大多数情况都受到了掌控，然而最近的情况彻底失控。在§Y [planet_target.GetName] §!发生的一场小型暴力事件随后变成了一场大暴动，如今整个星球上都动荡不安，暴力也在不断扩散，造成了大量伤亡。"
ADD utopia.3333.opt.a:0 "We must restore order!"
CN2 utopia.3333.opt.a:0 "我们必须恢复秩序！"
ADD utopia.3334.name:0 "Whisperers in the Void: §RPsychosis§!"
CN2 utopia.3334.name:0 "虚空低语者：§R精神错乱§!"
ADD utopia.3334.desc:0 "Ever since we invited the Whisperers into our minds, mental illness and unexplainable acts of violence have been on the rise among our psionic population. For the most part, it has been controllable, but recently things have gotten out of hand. A minor violent incident on §Y[planet_target.GetName]§! turned into a riot, and now the unrest and violence is spreading all across the planet, causing a great deal of death and destruction."
CN2 utopia.3334.desc:0 "自从我们邀请低语者进入我们的意识以来，精神疾病以及无法解释的暴力行为在我们的灵能人口中不断发生。大多数情况都受到了掌控，然而最近的情况彻底失控。在§Y [planet_target.GetName] §!发生的一场小型暴力事件随后变成了一场大暴动，如今整个星球上都动荡不安，暴力也在不断扩散，造成了大量伤亡。"
ADD utopia.3334.opt.a:0 "Terrible!"
CN2 utopia.3334.opt.a:0 "太糟糕了！"
ADD utopia.3335.name:0 "Eater of Worlds: §RPeckish§!"
CN2 utopia.3335.name:0 "世界吞噬者：§R腹中无物§!"
ADD utopia.3335.desc:0 "Once again, the Eater has returned to claim its tribute, devouring a whole city on §Y[planet_target.GetName]§!. Though we have been able to keep our covenant with the Eater secret from the population at large, the remaining people on the planet are understandable fearful and angry over these 'mysterious disappearances' and are demanding an explanation from the government."
CN2 utopia.3335.desc:0 "吞噬者又一次来收取它的贡品，吞噬了§Y [planet_target.GetName] §!一整座城市。尽管我们一直隐瞒着我们跟吞噬者的苟且不让民众们知道，但是星球上的人民对这些"神秘失踪"开始感到恐惧和不满，并要求政府为此做出解释。"
ADD utopia.3335.opt.a:0 "It was necessary."
CN2 utopia.3335.opt.a:0 "这是必要的牺牲。"
ADD utopia.3336.name:0 "Eater of Worlds: §RFamished§!"
CN2 utopia.3336.name:0 "世界吞噬者：§R饥肠辘辘§!"
ADD utopia.3336.desc:0 "Once again, the Eater has returned to claim its tribute, devouring a significant part of the population on §Y[planet_target.GetName]§!. Though we have been able to keep our covenant with the Eater secret from the population at large, the remaining people on the planet are understandable fearful and angry over these 'mysterious disappearances' and are demanding an explanation from the government."
CN2 utopia.3336.desc:0 "吞噬者又一次来收取它的贡品，吞噬了§Y [planet_target.GetName] §!的大量人口。尽管我们一直隐瞒着我们跟吞噬者的苟且不让民众们知道，但是星球上的人民对这些"神秘失踪"开始感到恐惧和不满，并要求政府为此做出解释。"
ADD utopia.3336.opt.a:0 "Regrettable, but unavoidable."
CN2 utopia.3336.opt.a:0 "令人遗憾，但无法避免。"
ADD utopia.3337.name:0 "Eater of Worlds: §RRavenous§!"
CN2 utopia.3337.name:0 "世界吞噬者：§R欲壑难填§!"
ADD utopia.3337.desc:0 "Once again, the Eater has returned to claim its tribute. Not content to merely claim a part of our population, the Eater has devoured a whole planet - not just its people, but animals, buildings... everything. §Y[planet_target.GetName]§! has been enveloped in a thick psionic fog, and rescue ships sent into the atmosphere have all failed to return. The loss of the planet is sending shockwaves across our empire, with citizens and local leaders alike demanding the government find an explanation for this cataclysmic event."
CN2 utopia.3337.desc:0 "吞噬者又一次来收取它的贡品了。这次它已不满足于得到一部分人口，而是吞噬了整座行星——不仅是人民，还有动物、建筑……所有的一切。§Y [planet_target.GetName] §!已经被一阵浓稠的灵能雾所笼罩，派入大气层的救援船也都有去无回。损失一座星球对整个帝国造成了一场冲击波，人民和当地领导一致要求政府就此浩劫作出解释。"
ADD utopia.3337.opt.a:0 "A high price to pay..."
CN2 utopia.3337.opt.a:0 "真是高昂的代价啊……"
ADD utopia.3338.name:0 "Instrument of Desire: §RParticularism§!"
CN2 utopia.3338.name:0 "欲望操纵者：§R特殊主义§!"
ADD utopia.3338.desc:0 "The desires inflicted upon our people by the Instrument are strong. The people of §Y[planet_target.GetName]§! have become convinced that their own particular customs are of distinct and paramount importance over those of our society as a whole. Alternative political movements are springing up like wildfire, and the political situation on the planet has become unpredictable, to say the least."
CN2 utopia.3338.desc:0 "操纵者对人们欲望所施加的影响颇为强大。§Y [planet_target.GetName] §!的人民坚信自己的个人需求远远重要过社会整体。政治更替运动如野火燎原。星球上的政治形势已经变得诡异莫测。"
ADD utopia.3338.opt.a:0 "Unfortunate."
CN2 utopia.3338.opt.a:0 "不幸。"
ADD utopia.3339.name:0 "Instrument of Desire: §RDeviance§!"
CN2 utopia.3339.name:0 "欲望操纵者：§R异端§!"
ADD utopia.3339.desc:0 "The desires inflicted upon our people by the Instrument are strong. As if overnight, the population of our empire appear to have turned against both the government and the very traditions of our people, questioning ages-old customs and breaking social taboos. Support for government positions are rapidly dropping, and it seems we may be in for a period of considerable political turmoil."
CN2 utopia.3339.desc:0 "操纵者对人们欲望所施加的影响颇为强大。仿佛一夜之间，帝国的人口都开始同时抵制政府，摒弃民族的传统美德，质疑历史悠久的习俗并试图打破所有社会禁忌。政府支持度急剧下跌，看来我们陷入了一场规模宏大的政治动乱。"
ADD utopia.3339.opt.a:0 "Terrible!"
CN2 utopia.3339.opt.a:0 "太糟糕了！"
ADD utopia.3340.name:0 "Instrument of Desire: §RDecadence§!"
CN2 utopia.3340.name:0 "欲望操纵者：§R堕落§!"
ADD utopia.3340.desc:0 "The desires inflicted upon our people by the Instrument are strong. The people of §Y[planet_target.GetName]§! have been caught in a frenzy of consumerism and decadence, demanding ever more exclusive goods, ever rarer and more savory foods. Already rioting has broken out at several shopping districts, and we have been forced to ramp up the production of our farms and industries to prevent the planet from descending into chaos."
CN2 utopia.3340.desc:0 "操纵者对人们欲望所施加的影响颇为强大。§Y [planet_target.GetName] §!的人民都变成了堕落的消费狂，不断要求享用更多的奢侈物品和更稀有美味的食物。在几个商业区中已经发生了暴动，我们不得不增加农业和工业产值以防止星球陷入一片混沌。"
ADD utopia.3340.opt.a:0 "Regrettable."
CN2 utopia.3340.opt.a:0 "真是遗憾啊。"
ADD utopia.3341.name:0 "Composer of Strands: §RMutation§!"
CN2 utopia.3341.name:0 "丝状体编织者：§R突变§!"
ADD utopia.3341.desc:0 "The §YComposer of Strands§! has bestowed its blessings upon us, directly altering the genetic code of the §Y[species_target.GetName]§! species. Strangely, the rapid and unpredictable mutations have provoked no more than a very muted reaction. It seems our population has to come to treat the random and unpredictable mutations as little more than a normal part of life, hardly worthy of outrage, or even discussion."
CN2 utopia.3341.desc:0 "§Y丝状体编织者§!赐予了我们它的庇佑，直接修改了§Y [species_target.GetName] §!的基因序列。奇怪的是，如此剧烈而难以预料的突变并没有造成社会巨大的反响。人们似乎已经将这种随机而变幻莫测的基因突变纳入平凡无奇的日常，完全没有感到愤怒，甚至连稍加讨论都没有。"
ADD utopia.3341.opt.a:0 "Let us see what the results are..."
CN2 utopia.3341.opt.a:0 "静待其变吧……"
ADD utopia.200.name:0 "A New Presence in the Shroud"
CN2 utopia.200.name:0 "灵能界的新兴存在"
ADD utopia.200.desc.a:0 "A change has come over the [target_species.GetNamePlural] living in our empire. It started with a faint ripple in the Shroud. Now it's as if they are vibrating on a different level. We all feel it, the [target_species.GetNamePlural] are on the verge of developing latent psionic abilities, similar to our own.\n\nMaybe it's from living in such close proximity to us. Maybe the Shroud has simply chosen them. The Conclave of Telepaths, our chief psionic experts, warn us that this may be our only chance to intervene. We could nip it in the bud or help them awaken. They won't get far without our guidance."
CN2 utopia.200.desc.a:0 "生活在我们帝国内的 [target_species.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 发生了一些变化。一开始是灵能界出现的细微波动涟漪，逐渐地剧增到现在的猛烈颤动。我们所有人都能感觉到 [target_species.GetNamePlural] 快要进化出跟我们相似的潜在灵能能力了。\n\n或许是因为长期跟我们亲近的原因，也许是因为灵能界冥冥中选中了他们。通灵会提示我们，此时此刻是我们最后的净化机会。我们可以选择能断绝他们的觉醒之路，或者选择助他们一臂之力。没有我们指引的话，他们的前景不容乐观。"
ADD utopia.200.desc.b:0 "Unusual activity in the Shroud suggests that another species in our nation, the [target_species.GetNamePlural], are beginning to manifest latent psionic abilities. We are now faced with the same choice as before - will we suppress or unleash their burgeoning powers?"
CN2 utopia.200.desc.b:0 "灵能界最近的异常动向表明着国内又有一个种族的灵能能力正在觉醒，这次是轮到 [target_species.GetNamePlural] 。我们面临跟以往一样的选择，是扼杀于摇篮中？还是解放他们正在萌芽的力量？"
ADD utopia.200.a:0 "We will unlock their potential."
CN2 utopia.200.a:0 "我们会释放他们的潜力。"
ADD utopia.200.a.tooltip:0 "All [target_species.GetAdj] pops will gain the trait §YLatent Psionic§!."
CN2 utopia.200.a.tooltip:0 "所有 [target_species.GetAdj] 人口获得特性§Y潜在灵能能力§!。"
ADD utopia.200.b:0 "They are unworthy."
CN2 utopia.200.b:0 "他们不配。"
ADD utopia.203.name:0 "The Awakening"
CN2 utopia.203.name:0 "觉醒"
ADD utopia.203.desc.a:0 "Under the guidance of the Conclave of Telepaths, the [target_species.GetNamePlural] have developed a deeper connection to the Shroud than we could ever have imagined. It's as if these powers were meant for them all along.\n\nNow they claim to be ready to unlock their full psionic potential. The conclave however is divided. Some are worried that the change has come too fast and that their minds would become unstable, others that their newfound powers could go to their heads. But if we don't strike now, we may never get another chance."
CN2 utopia.203.desc.a:0 "在通灵会的指引下， [target_species.GetNamePlural] 跟灵能界建立了出乎我们意料的深层联系，就好像这些力量就是为他们而生的一样。\n\n他们现在声称自己已经准备好释放自己全部的潜在灵能了。但是通灵会的人却分裂成两种声音。有些人担心变化来得太快，对方的心灵可能会变得不稳定；另一部分人则认为对方可能会变得野心膨胀。我们要是不马上采取行动，恐怕以后都不会再有机会了。"
ADD utopia.203.desc.b:0 "The [target_species.GetNamePlural] too claim that they are ready to take the steps needed to reach their full psionic potential and be awoken."
CN2 utopia.203.desc.b:0 " [target_species.GetNamePlural] 也同样声称自己已经完全准备好唤醒自己所有的潜在灵能了。"
ADD utopia.203.a:0 "They are ready."
CN2 utopia.203.a:0 "他们的确是准备好了。"
ADD utopia.203.a.tooltip:0 "All [target_species.GetAdj] pops will gain the trait §YPsionic§!."
CN2 utopia.203.a.tooltip:0 "所有 [target_species.GetAdj] 人口获得特性§Y灵能§!。"
ADD utopia.203.b:0 "They are unworthy."
CN2 utopia.203.b:0 "他们不配。"
ADD utopia.203.c:0 "It's too dangerous."
CN2 utopia.203.c:0 "这么做实在太冒险了。"
ADD utopia.204.name:0 "A Rude Awakening"
CN2 utopia.204.name:0 "狂暴的觉醒"
ADD utopia.204.desc.a:0 "Lately our researchers have been perplexed by the unexpected manifestation of psionic abilities in some [original_species.GetSpeciesNamePlural]. Upon investigation they found that these changes coincided with a major psionic awakening of their brethren in the [target_country.GetName], a nation that has long been known for its prowess within the field of psionics.\n\nWe can only assume that some of their newfound powers have bled over to their distant relatives in our empire, through means we don't yet understand."
CN2 utopia.204.desc.a:0 "我们的研究员最近对部分 [original_species.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 身上突然冒现的灵能能力感到困惑不解。研究员在仔细调查后发现这些变化与他们在 [target_country.GetName] 的同胞的一场集体灵能觉醒有关，该国向来是以拥有超凡的灵能方面的造诣而闻名。\n\n我们只能猜想对方的这种新发现的觉醒能力是通过了某种我们无法理解的方式‘感染’到了对方居住在我国的远亲。"
ADD utopia.204.desc.b:0 "Lately our researchers have been perplexed by the unexpected manifestation of psionic abilities in some [original_species.GetSpeciesNamePlural]. Upon closer examination they found that the psionics are linked telepathically to their brethren in a previously unknown nation, the [target_country.GetName], with which we have now established communications. It seems the changes we've experienced were a ripple effect, brought on by a major psionic awakening of all [original_species.GetSpeciesNamePlural] in [target_country.GetName]."
CN2 utopia.204.desc.b:0 "我们的研究员最近对部分 [original_species.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 身上突然冒现的灵能能力感到困惑不解。研究员在仔细调查后发现这些灵能能力是跟他们远在新发现的 [target_country.GetName] 国的远亲有着心灵联系。看来这些觉醒是由 [target_country.GetName] 的所有 [original_species.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 的集体灵能觉醒事件所引发的连锁反应。"
ADD utopia.204.a.tooltip:0 "Up to 4 [original_species.GetSpeciesAdj] pops will get the trait §Ylatent psionic§!."
CN2 utopia.204.a.tooltip:0 "最多4个 [original_species.GetSpeciesAdj] 人口会获得特性§Y潜在灵能§!。"
ADD utopia.205.name:0 "An Unexpected Awakening"
CN2 utopia.205.name:0 "出乎意料的觉醒"
ADD utopia.205.desc:0 "Since the psionic awakening of the [target_species.GetName], our informants report that some individuals belonging to the same species elsewhere, have also begun to show signs of latent psionic abilities. It is as if their common ancestry links them in the Shroud, regardless of the physical distance between them.\n\nUnlike their distant relatives in our nation however, they are few and far between, and it is unlikely they'll ever reach a full awakening."
CN2 utopia.205.desc:0 "自 [target_species.GetName] 灵能觉醒之后，我们的情报显示该种族居住在银河各个角落的同胞也开始显现觉醒潜在灵能的迹象。感觉像是他们的相同血脉把他们所有人都紧紧联系在灵能界中，无论他们在现实世界中身处何方。\n\n跟居住于我国境内的同胞不同，这些漂泊在银河各地的远亲因为数量太过稀少，或许永远都无法完成觉醒。"
